What is shell scripting?
Shell scripting is a progmamming language using which a set of instructions can be written in a file to instruct the Kernel using shell.

What is #!/bin/bash ?
This is first line which is written in a shell script to define the shell we intend to use. This is also know as shebang. And the shell used is Bourne again shell.
By default if the first line is skipped the #!/bin/sh is used. 

Write a Shell Script which prints I will complete #90DaysOofDevOps challenge 
#!/bin/sh
echo "I will complete #90DaysOofDevOps challenge"

Write a Shell Script to take user input, input from arguments and print the variables.
#!/bin/bash
echo "Enter value"
read a
string1=10
echo "The user input is $a"
echo "The variable used in this script is $string1 and the argument passed by the user is $1"

Write an Example of If else in Shell Scripting by comparing 2 numbers
#!/bin/sh
if [ $1 -gt $2 ]
then
        echo "$1 is greater than $2"
elif [ $1 -lt $2 ]
then 
        echo "$1 is less than $2"
else
        echo " $1 equals $2"
fi
